It’s the first snow of the season & I spent time with old journals. I found a draft I wrote, that I later put on craigslist as I sought housemates. I was 22 and while it’s reassuring that parts of me haven’t changed, I wonder what that that version of me would think of me now. Would he be glad I wasn’t a poor punk anymore and could afford to properly heat in the winter or would he wonder if I got lazy about my ethics and duties as an activist? Would he be proud of the overall story arch that finally pushed me to connect with nature as I had always dreamed? Or would he be sad that even though I overcame so much and was living a version of a vision that I always wanted... would he ache at the unimaginable, that somehow community & connection had come and gone & was no longer abundant. Would he understand my choices to lock myself away for awhile? #storytime #vintage #writer #mentalhealth #queer #cabinlife #pennsylvania #philly #philadelphia

Someone commented surprise in learning more about my design past from a recent reel showing a designy product of mine…. So I’ll share that my life before this I was an artist/designer/maker/small biz owner. Happy accidents led me there and it was the most stressful fun I ever had. Always wanting to connect myself to nature, I got my start with a silly idea for wood watches but specifically wanted to create a soft flexible wood band. You can scroll through and see prototypes and a few nice shots of some of the final designs. Eventually I designed watches from marble, moss, flowers, and cork. My former baby was “Inspirer by Nature” and while what I’m doing now in my life is much more crunchy… it’s still pretty “on brand” in the nature aspect. Anyway, I’m glad that part of my life is over it was a constant hustle but I learned a lot. #design

That was day 220 today is day 606. I thought I’d be in a different place at this point but healing isn’t linear and personal strength can hard to hold constantly. Not to mention unpacking the deep deep stuff, facing how it impacted your life in the more sinister subtle ways, and contending with constant self doubt - am I distracting, is this a part of the process, why am I not where I want to be yet, am I just lacking gratitude for what’s in front of me now, etc etc. Personal growth and overcoming your challenges means crafting a journey of recovery that’s fit best for you - but let me tell ya what, I’m still not sure I’m doing the right thing in the right place at the right time and in part it’s because while it’s beautiful here and videos have audio and look fun there’s a lot I don’t show. There’s a lot most don’t show. Last year was hard. Be gentler on others and yourself, turn envy into drive, and keep on keeping on. #selflove #journey #recovery #anxiety #healing #cabinlife #pennsylvania #trauma #queer #growth

For the first time in over 3 years, and after 600 days at my cabin, I made a recent escape. Was in LA and Hawaii and the trip started by opening my carry on to discover it was full of someone else’s dirty laundry. I never did get my bag back & I will never have a simple black carry on again - but I did have fun making island clothes, socializing, eating meals I didn’t cook myself, etc. Long and short, last year was rough but I think I’ve set the stage for this year to be better. I saw massive waves, hung out with horses, caught up with some friends, toured a friends fruit farm, did some hikes, did a little karioke, and I needed this. Maybe more than I realize. Anyway, happy new year 🤙 sit tight as I try to maintain these vibes moving forward #gaycation

👋❤️Just a reminder that your timeline doesn’t need to look like others and that the best way to handle not achieving things you thought you wanted is by removing the expectations around the goal. Expect less, be disappointed less. Hold gratitude for what you do have and the strengths you’ve got. If you want something, look at it as a flower in your hand. If you hold it too tight, you’ll kill it… you must hold it loosely. The flower is your own expectations, progress, goals, wants, etc. Sure there things are all good frameworks and targets but at the end of the day you must fortify yourself most in a way that ensures you stay protected. Mentally, you’ll be stronger for not requiring/expecting/insisting on certain outcomes. The suffering can come from seeing what isn’t, as opposed to what is. #mentalhealth #recovery #selfcare #30s #adulting #buddhism #goals #expectations #gratitude

Let me re-introduce myself, and explain to you how we are alike. I’m a 35 year old “grown up adult” who moved alone to the woods so he could actually finally do the “grown up” work of dealing with my internal issues. Along the way I’ve challenged myself in ways I never imagined but that’s besides the point. We are the same you and I. Is our trauma the same? No. Age? Probably not. Privilege? Probably not. What is the same tho, is that you and I exist in a world that prioritizing productivity, excess, status, and wealth. Here’s the thing though - all of those items really tie back to the same human desire, and that is security. Some people are born with safe families that teach them how to handle emotions, that’s a sense of security. Some people push others away to protect themselves from hurt, that’s a sense of security. Some people go to medical school so they can have financial security and security in their sense of purpose. We all want security and we all have different needs and hurdles to get that, but I promise you, security is a frame of mind. I’m not saying it’s easy, it takes work, it takes commitment to gratitude, it takes rounding up to good instead of bad, and it often takes letting go and forgetting the past. It takes being naive enough to trust you’ll build a better future. You need to find what works for you, you need to know others are struggling for the same thing even if they literally look like they are living a dream life online. I am struggling. I’m tired. I’ve tried a lot and lost a lot, but I at least know what matters most - and that is security. If you are lost, let a sense of security be your North Star and if you have a healthy dose of security share the wealth. Seriously, sharing the wealth… time, sensitivity, giving, extending, loving, forgiving… all of that wealth, when you share it - it will even increase your own sense of security in yourself. Keep on keeping on friends and do not ever let your own security come at the cost of robbing another of theirs. #selflove #selfcare #givingback #security #cptsd #faith #focus #youarenotalone #youarenotyourthoughts #natureheals #recoveryjourney

I’ve been afraid to share this level of raw emotion because I know people can see and hear and know that under all of these words is a lot of suffering… and that this level of it takes a lot of loss and grief… but I don’t want pity, I know when I’m in a good place I can round up to good and honor gratitude, I know when life feels good I eventually see the value in the dark days, but I’m sharing this because I know so many others feel this too. So many others are tired of the seasons, so many of us don’t know unconditional love and while it’s our job to correct our own maladaptive parts of ourselves so that we can receive unconditional love, the facts are that it’s not a level playing field. We don’t all have the same safety net or background that offers us the ability to view people as seasons & just move on quickly, and for the vast majority of humans existing the villages and the tribes we knew, remained constant. If you have been gifted with abundance, understand that also means you are more likely to allow people to exist as seasons and it’s your job as a human to ensure that if you make the unspoken promise to be a season to someone you find love and beauty in because you see their vulnerability, know that their vulnerability and big heart came at a major cost to them. We need to stop acting like it’s normal to push people out and just move on, human bonds are meant to be stronger than that and yes of course some people need to be let go but you can consciously, in a healthy cadence, together agree to make that happen. Cutting out or shutting down might work for you, but that’s a maladaptive skill set. We have these brains and logic and language… why do we not negotiate the entrance and exits in life with grace? Being there for someone doesn’t have to mean you take on their burden, it means you value and honor the history and the bond that did exist so you work together to find a way to reduce the harm and hurt from the change of the season. Do not enter ones life, fall in love with the richness and depth there that came from so much hardship and overcoming to just disregard their humanity. No one ever knows how many seasons are left. #love

I’m a much bigger idea person than a doer - but I guess before it gets done, it’s gotta be ideated and if I don’t feel I’ve explored every option… it kinda makes me insecure about a choice. Ah, seems quirky? I think it comes from a deep seeded fear of making the wrong choice and being unhappy with the outcome, which probably stems from the experienced regrets and failures from the past. The truth is, there are so many things that never happen because we get stuck in the fear based phases of things. Seriously, fear and love impact every aspect of our lives. Am I afraid of a retro exterior? Do I love the idea of enclosing in my porch? Will I get bored with pattern or have the stamina to cut so many unique and beautiful shingles? 👏🎬 if I only had a crew on hand to execute for me 🤣 That would give me a hard deadline and I’d have to make decisions but since I’m doing all the work boy oh boy I’ve noticed how easy it is to get stuck. Sometimes you need a crew to move ahead, sometimes we don’t notice how fear impacts even small things. This is highly internal - what may look like someone loving them self and going inwards, to them might be fear of being around others and being disappointed. What’s wild is that - both perspectives are valid and so if inside YOUR HEAD I am winning, how do I plant that idea inside my own head? Thoughts? 🤔#diy #retro #cabinlife #cabinfruit #homerenovation #design

Y’all know how thrifty I am right? Y’all also know that I’m a jerk of all trades too yeah? Well, many trades. I’m also quite averse to uh… a traditional job as I’m still focused on my own well being and mental health. Have you ever wanted to pick my brain? So I think I’ve decided to enclose my porch and build storage in the main room (will close off my bedroom door, entrance will be from porch) all of this so I can have a proper studio as well as moisture safe storage for tools etc. Which means, I can be better at being consistent and having a dedicated space to explore/make etc. SO… I was thinking, and I feel weird even saying this, but if you’ve seen my stories enough you know my credentials… (small biz, design, self care, communication, etc) but was thinking offering 50min of my time for say $75-120 an hour sliding scale. Would anyone be into this to help me fund enclosing my porch? You can probe about cabin life, ask about pitching to investors, show me your small space and ask for ideas, you can present your business to me & I can give you the road map, we can talk social growth strategies, or cats, I used to teach business and ran a design studio in another life, I’ve also been a head of marketing, an amateur wood worker, raised money on Kickstarter to launch projects, community organizer and activist, and EXPERT at being thrifty etc. The most expensive part of this would be windows which I’ll source used anyway… so ANYWAY would anyone pay little ol’ me for 50 min and we can chit chat, or turn the camera on and dance together on zoom, or you pitch a product idea & maybe it wets my whistle to get involved, really anything you want that isn’t creepy and makes me feel weird and uncomfortable. Spring is near… which means lots of projects too, but I’m tired and quite lonely these days and at the same time have sort of given up on trying to connect with people like I have in the past. It took a lot of wounds for me to end up out here, and new ones since being here. Mostly emotional… loss I can’t speak about, but physicals too. I have a pinched shoulder thing that won’t go away, keeping up with socials and video and tech can be exhausting but at least I feel some degree of connection, the news is chaotic and queer life is being attacked, and sometimes I just wish I could hire builders and painters or a mad scientist to build a Time Machine. Sometimes I wish that American health care wasn’t a mess and I could actually have my shoulder issue identified and properly sorted. I miss community and dates but I’m having a hard time connecting with anyone. In a lot of ways, I never left the pandemic mode we were in. I mean I moved out here 2 years ago and also had a good 14 months of pandemic life in the city. This has been the loneliest period of my life and I’m doing my best but I often think about quitting. Existential dread, often have a what’s the point attitude, about a lot of things. Energy levels are low, they have been for some time, and I’m struggling being optimistic right now. I turn 36 soon and I’m not ready. Where did time go? Hard to ease the inner child when you honestly would be afraid to tell him of how life went and where you are. I know it’s pretty here and music to video makes this wondrous, but it’s hard. My life was very hard for nearly all but maybe 8 years or so. I don’t know when the universe is going to give back but JFC I want to be happy and whole and it does often feel like others in life can impact you so deeply that it robs you of the ability to achieve that. yeah, just being real and cranky and tired and anxious #cabinlife #cottagecore #pennsylvania

Nature is healing on a cellular and protein production level. Phytoncides from trees are believed to be what is so beneficial. Phytoncide exposure significantly increased NK activity, the percentages of NK, perforin, granulysin, and granzyme A/B-expressing cells, and significantly decreases the percentage of T cells. In one study, gallbladder patients recovered a day earlier when their room window faced trees versus not. #healing #nature

Y’all today while foraging I found this baby near a storks nest out in the woods. Should I keep him? I want to, my brovaries are on fire! He was so much more than just a smiling bag of potato. I would probably pay for “baby therapy” and honestly men in general are so far removed from opportunities to engage with or celebrate babies and I myself don’t think I’ve held a baby this young ever, it was very special to hold him - brought me very much into that present moment and for a little while made the rest of the world melt away. My ex partners sister had easy pregnancies and had offered to carry a child for us - and for the first time in my life it had occurred to me that I could have a biological child with a male partner and that child could be tied to both of us DNA wise. I had long ago, as most gay men do, mourned the idea of having my own birth children and the last year I let go of the idea of being a dad for a number of reasons, one being that it hurts to hold onto something tightly. I think it’s easier to let that idea go if you have nieces and nephews, but this was a real treat today. 🐣

Im anxious to write this raw… but I have often over the last two years stood and looked out this window so broken.. or I’d hear what sounded like a car and wishfully hop up and look… and always find the road empty. I can’t count number of times I’ve specifically asked for people (people I had a known & had a baseline previously of knowing I felt safe with them) who I saw as family (chosen or actual) to change and show up to only be disappointed. Metaphorically I’ve asked people to do the work on themselves and show up that way, and it’s the same. I’ve learned you can not have any expectations of anyone, and that even if you have the best interest at heart people won’t see that if you push away, shut down, lash out, etc. People lack bandwidth to maintain consistent empathy. Cancer patients lose all their friends, people getting divorced feel alone and their hurt minimized. People take things personally or are so ashamed of their impact they will not confront you or show up because that means admittance of their impact or front on facing hard truths. Almost always the hard truths is that both sides messed up. I have messed up so many times in so many ways, putting pressure over compassion, just hoping the core of who I am is what people hold in their mind to always bring them center about me but people aren’t wired like this. If anything it takes people time to be aware of their bias, villainizing, fear of failure and shame, etc. and then it takes even longer for them to realize how that impacted how or if they showed up.. up to a relationship, a place, a person. This is a painful truth of life today & as I’m nearly at 700 days alone here I am still finding I need to make big change to handle big problems, so I don’t know what to do but I know that I’m sorry to anyone I’ve hurt, I’m sorry I couldn’t hold compassion for you & took things personally when I shouldn’t have, & I’m sorry you couldn’t hold compassion for me and took things personally when you shouldn’t have. Y’all life can be so hard sometimes… and it’s so very sad that so many people don’t show up for you or do the work for themselves which also ends up benefiting you. Take care of yourself. #healing
I’m sorry we couldn’t hold compassion for each other & we took things personally when we shouldn’t have. #healing #recovery #loss

Not photoshop - when I was 19 I went to south america to travel alone for 3 months. I told enough people before I got a ticket, which compelled me to pull the trigger. My lease was ending & my personal problems had not resolved themselves, I had worked all the year before & was still sorting out my future. I figured without a rent expense and some savings that i'd throw myself into the unknown. I was mending a broken heart, trying to find myself, and this during map quest days and was before iphones. I barely spoke spanish & i traveled with quite literally the smallest backpack i'd seen any other backpacker travel with. It was a small canvas backpack from a military surplus - I wanted to make sure I reduced chances of getting robbed, I didn't want to look like a gringo backpacker. That tiny green bag held a notebook, a spanish dictionary, a digital camera, and a few shirts socks shorts and undies. I'd trade books at hostels and I grew my hair and beard out, the travel was often very lonely and by bus or vans but I read a lot, I remember namely The Alchemist and Dante's Inferno. This photo here is in Bolivia at the Salar de Uyuni a massive salt flat, covered with water at the time, and it truly felt like waking around an optical illusion. A sort of heaven for the mind and eyes. During this 3 month adventure I did a live work exchange at an animal refuge in the amazon basin too. Sometimes I feel like my life has changed so much, and sometimes I remember the things that have been a constant thread. #Travel #bolovia

Flowers in Myles dog bowl. ❤️ A college friend sent me flowers after Myles had passed. It made my day. I don't think i've ever gotten flowers before. As days have passed, i've pressed some, re-arranged some, put some in silica gel to dry them, and have some hung. It's felt like... a nice calming ritual in honor of him,  peaceful pensive process, almost to a degree that it feels like there is an opportunity here. I know how to do most of what was listed above, and in this photo i'm using a special stand meant for displaying flowers in a very shallow dish/plate. Creating a ritual out of a routine as days pass, it's felt kinda special. I wonder if this could be packaged into something others might find comfort in when mourning pet loss. I miss Myles, but i am finding comfort in the small things.

I don't know if I'll see flowers the same. This gift became a vehicle for so much more. A happenstance of the routine of care taking care of something accidentally... maybe out of need or habit..creating a gift of ritual, presence, & healing. What should I do with the pressed & hanging ones? When's the last time you sent someone flowers? These came from a very unexpected person and it was so much more than anyone from my past extended. Maybe people don't see pet loss the same, but Myles and I were a well known duo, and so I was just so grateful to have been thought of and given some joy in a dark time. I wanted to savor it I think.

If you have an abundance of love, be grateful. It's odd, how it can be glamorized - to be alone & away from people and places. Most people that are highly isolated, they have deep suffering. They could be unfamilied, elderly, friends could have all left, they could struggle with addiction, mental health issues, a disability, all of which could have contributed to losses that led them there, they could simply have fear to engage again because of past hurts and being alone feels safer. These people find relief from the suffering by finding ways to own being present, often forced to believe that love from only self has to be what fills up their cup. It's a lie, for most, that once you achieve purely self love you achieve peace and nirvana. Self love isn't enough for most, yet so many who have so much outer love don't really appreciate it. I think you see or become aware most clearly, when something isn't there. People that preach self love and presence as a cure all, are people who don't consider the complexity of the extent to which others lived a different level of experiences than them. The pain of being a human... with a hard history, with dreams passed, without people, with a changing brain and body, craving touch, losing self belief due to lack of nourishment, etc. It's sad to me that in this world where self care & mental health are spoken of as a priority, we put the onus on individuals to find and grant self love to themselves, it's the key, they say, and that is valued over bonds & community as what uplifts. The focus on self is so strong culturally and subversively that people think feeling bad for others situation is a "giving & empathetic" and enough. Really, it's a selfish pass to do what's easiest for themselves. Don't assume people want to be alone in hard times or that you'll say the wrong thing, just show up to the table & when you have abundance of love both self and outer, share it. Millions of people crave connection & can't access it anymore, self love is nothing but a mere coping mechanism of survival in lieu of existing within what is, and for most it's just not enough. #mentalhealth #alone #isolation #grief #recovery
